## Implementation Plan: Arcan CLI Persistent Configuration

### 1. Overview

The plan introduces a two-layer configuration system: a **TOML config file** for CLI bootstrap settings (Layer 1), and **Lago-backed SessionManifest propagation** for agent context (Layer 2). It adds `--provider` and `--model` as global CLI flags, introduces `arcan config`, `arcan status`, and `arcan stop` subcommands, and ensures full backward compatibility with the existing environment-variable workflow.

---

### 2. Config File Format and Loading

**File:** NEW `arcan/crates/arcan/src/config.rs`

The config file uses TOML for simplicity and fast parsing. Two locations are searched with project-local taking precedence over global:

1. **Project-local:** `.arcan/config.toml` (relative to CWD, resolved via `data_dir`)
2. **Global:** `~/.config/arcan/config.toml` (using the `dirs` crate for cross-platform `config_dir()`)

**Struct definition:**

```rust
use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
use std::collections::HashMap;
use std::path::{Path, PathBuf};

/// Top-level persistent configuration.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Default, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(default)]
pub struct ArcanConfig {
    pub defaults: DefaultsConfig,
    #[serde(default)]
    pub providers: HashMap<String, ProviderConfig>,
    #[serde(default)]
    pub agent: AgentConfig,
}

/// Default provider/model/port settings.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(default)]
pub struct DefaultsConfig {
    pub provider: Option<String>,
    pub model: Option<String>,
    pub port: Option<u16>,
    pub data_dir: Option<PathBuf>,
    pub session: Option<String>,
}

impl Default for DefaultsConfig {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            provider: None,
            model: None,
            port: None,
            data_dir: None,
            session: None,
        }
    }
}

/// Per-provider configuration (non-secret settings only).
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Default, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(default)]
pub struct ProviderConfig {
    pub model: Option<String>,
    pub base_url: Option<String>,
    pub max_tokens: Option<u32>,
    pub enable_streaming: Option<bool>,
}

/// Agent behavior configuration.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(default)]
pub struct AgentConfig {
    pub max_iterations: Option<u32>,
    pub approval_timeout: Option<u64>,
}

impl Default for AgentConfig {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            max_iterations: None,
            approval_timeout: None,
        }
    }
}
```

**Loading logic:**

```rust
impl ArcanConfig {
    /// Load config from project-local and global locations, merging them.
    /// Project-local settings override global settings.
    pub fn load(data_dir: &Path) -> Self {
        let local_path = data_dir.join("config.toml");
        let global_path = Self::global_config_path();

        let global = global_path.and_then(|p| Self::load_from_file(&p));
        let local = Self::load_from_file(&local_path);

        match (global, local) {
            (Some(g), Some(l)) => g.merge(l),
            (None, Some(l)) => l,
            (Some(g), None) => g,
            (None, None) => Self::default(),
        }
    }

    fn global_config_path() -> Option<PathBuf> {
        dirs::config_dir().map(|d| d.join("arcan").join("config.toml"))
    }

    fn load_from_file(path: &Path) -> Option<Self> {
        let content = std::fs::read_to_string(path).ok()?;
        toml::from_str(&content).ok()
    }

    /// Merge: `other` overrides `self` for any non-None fields.
    fn merge(mut self, other: Self) -> Self {
        // defaults
        if other.defaults.provider.is_some() { self.defaults.provider = other.defaults.provider; }
        if other.defaults.model.is_some() { self.defaults.model = other.defaults.model; }
        if other.defaults.port.is_some() { self.defaults.port = other.defaults.port; }
        if other.defaults.data_dir.is_some() { self.defaults.data_dir = other.defaults.data_dir; }
        if other.defaults.session.is_some() { self.defaults.session = other.defaults.session; }
        // providers: deep merge
        for (name, config) in other.providers {
            let entry = self.providers.entry(name).or_default();
            if config.model.is_some() { entry.model = config.model; }
            if config.base_url.is_some() { entry.base_url = config.base_url; }
            if config.max_tokens.is_some() { entry.max_tokens = config.max_tokens; }
            if config.enable_streaming.is_some() { entry.enable_streaming = config.enable_streaming; }
        }
        // agent
        if other.agent.max_iterations.is_some() { self.agent.max_iterations = other.agent.max_iterations; }
        if other.agent.approval_timeout.is_some() { self.agent.approval_timeout = other.agent.approval_timeout; }
        self
    }

    /// Write config to the project-local config file.
    pub fn save_local(&self, data_dir: &Path) -> anyhow::Result<()> {
        std::fs::create_dir_all(data_dir)?;
        let content = toml::to_string_pretty(self)?;
        std::fs::write(data_dir.join("config.toml"), content)?;
        Ok(())
    }
}
```

**Key design decisions:**
- All fields are `Option<T>` to support partial configs and merging
- No secrets (API keys) in config files -- they stay in env vars
- `toml` crate is fast, pure Rust, zero network calls
- The `dirs` crate provides cross-platform `~/.config/` resolution

