### 11. Risks and Mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| Config file write race if two CLI invocations run simultaneously | Use atomic write (write to temp file, then rename) in `save_local()` |
| Daemon doesn't pick up config changes after restart | Daemon reads config at startup; document that `arcan stop && arcan serve` reloads config |
| Breaking change if `--port` default behavior changes | The hardcoded default of 3000 stays as the fallback when no config/env/flag is set |
| `dirs` crate adds a dependency | `dirs` is tiny (4 crates, pure Rust) and widely used; no concern |
| Config file gets committed with secrets | Document in generated config that API keys go in env vars; add `.arcan/config.toml` to `.gitignore` guidance |

